15:30.407 --> 15:32.627
♪ She was made

15:32.670 --> 15:35.804
♪ To blow you away

15:35.847 --> 15:38.111
♪ She don't care

15:38.154 --> 15:41.810
♪ What any man say

15:41.853 --> 15:43.159
[IGNITION CLICKS OFF] ♪ You can watch her strut

15:45.031 --> 15:47.511
♪ But keep your mouth shut

15:47.555 --> 15:52.603
♪ Or it's ruination day

15:52.647 --> 15:54.692
♪ Well, now, she's long

15:58.783 --> 16:00.872
♪ Long gone

16:06.966 --> 16:07.923
Well, well, well.

16:08.576 --> 16:10.186
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

16:10.230 --> 16:12.014
Been a little
AWOL, Morris.

16:13.146 --> 16:14.408
I got in
a motor vehicle accident.

16:15.365 --> 16:17.237
I was hospitalized.

16:17.280 --> 16:18.455
You okay?

16:21.502 --> 16:23.417
Yeah, I am now.
Was out of it a few days.

16:25.419 --> 16:27.290
Come on in.

16:27.334 --> 16:28.161
I just made some stew.

16:35.211 --> 16:36.125
[GROANS SOFTLY]

16:41.087 --> 16:43.045
Wow.
Been painting a lot?

16:43.089 --> 16:45.439
Well, gotta protect
my sanity somehow.

16:55.449 --> 16:56.189
[CLEARS THROAT SOFTLY]

17:05.415 --> 17:06.851
You ain't
talking much.

17:08.549 --> 17:11.378
Something tells me we have
more than a few topics
for discussion.

17:19.386 --> 17:21.997
I fucked up
in a very
monumental way.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.043
Well, we either
go big or go home.

17:41.930 --> 17:43.584
I can't even bring myself
to say it out loud.

17:43.627 --> 17:44.715
It's too awful.

17:44.759 --> 17:46.195
You killed John Rothstein.

17:48.415 --> 17:50.069
You think I'm daft?

17:50.112 --> 17:52.854
I was the one who told you
about those manuscripts,

17:52.897 --> 17:55.030
him hoarding cash.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.640
I can do the math.

17:56.684 --> 17:58.512
I tell you
what he's got stashed.

17:58.555 --> 18:01.167
Suddenly he's dead
and you're MIA.

18:01.210 --> 18:04.474
Two plus two equals
"you shot John Rothstein
in the head."

18:08.957 --> 18:10.872
It wasn't my intent.
He pulled out a gun.

18:10.915 --> 18:12.003
He shot at me.
It happened...

18:13.353 --> 18:15.659
[SIGHS]
So fast.

18:15.703 --> 18:16.965
I swear it was
self-defense.

18:17.008 --> 18:19.141
Self-defense
in your eyes, maybe.

18:19.185 --> 18:21.926
In the eyes of the law,
felony murder.

18:27.715 --> 18:28.977
So you got
the manuscripts?

18:34.113 --> 18:35.331
No.

18:39.640 --> 18:41.816
I got in the accident
fleeing the scene.
I crashed in a ditch.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.561
While I was in the hospital,
somebody came
across the car...

18:50.172 --> 18:51.565
Took the money
and the manuscripts.

18:54.176 --> 18:55.743
What?

18:55.786 --> 18:56.787
I don't got them...

18:58.354 --> 18:59.616
Nor the money.

18:59.660 --> 19:01.531
You don't have
the manuscripts?

19:03.098 --> 19:04.273
No.

19:05.405 --> 19:07.407
So when you said
"monumental fuckup,"

19:07.450 --> 19:10.323
you were selling yourself
short, Morris.

19:10.366 --> 19:14.283
You might've set yourself
a Guinness world record
for fuckups.

19:14.327 --> 19:16.198
I have half a mind to turn
my gun on myself.

19:16.242 --> 19:17.547
Well, we won't
be doing that.

19:17.591 --> 19:18.461
I killed him.

19:20.768 --> 19:22.770
Alma, I killed him,
my God.

19:22.813 --> 19:25.076
Okay, look.

19:25.120 --> 19:26.208
First...

19:27.775 --> 19:29.168
You did the man,

19:29.211 --> 19:30.865
and maybe the world,
a favor.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.998
He couldn't write
for shit anymore.

19:34.042 --> 19:37.437
You allowed him to go out
in a bit of gory glory,

19:37.480 --> 19:39.221
which, trust me,
that's exactly what
he would've wanted.

19:40.483 --> 19:42.398
And his fans
get to cling to him

19:42.442 --> 19:45.880
as this eccentric,
bigger-than-life icon

19:45.923 --> 19:47.925
when in fact,
his mind and his dick

19:47.969 --> 19:50.232
were in a race to see
which could shrivel up faster.

19:51.842 --> 19:53.017
Morris, look at me.

19:56.891 --> 19:59.198
He was a mean old man.

20:01.374 --> 20:02.679
As somebody who loved him,

20:04.246 --> 20:05.421
who was loved by him,

20:06.901 --> 20:08.207
I'm telling you,

20:08.990 --> 20:11.601
he had it coming

20:11.645 --> 20:14.213
for a very long time.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.262
Your bigger crime here
was losing those books.

20:20.306 --> 20:21.220
I know that.

20:24.527 --> 20:27.095
Never mind what they're worth.
The chance to read them...

20:27.138 --> 20:29.445
You gotta find who took them.
You need to get them back.

20:31.665 --> 20:33.101
I plan to.How?

20:35.321 --> 20:37.714
I don't know yet,
but I will.

20:37.758 --> 20:39.629
I'm gonna think on this,

20:39.673 --> 20:41.457
and I'm gonna
help you, Morris.

20:46.462 --> 20:47.550
But, Morris...

20:49.422 --> 20:52.425
For something
this important,

20:52.468 --> 20:55.297
I'll need to do
my very best thinking.

20:58.648 --> 21:00.694
I'll need all my acuity,

21:00.737 --> 21:02.261
good blood flow,

21:03.871 --> 21:05.525
to my brain,
to everywhere.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.267
I need full circulation.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.445
You know what
I'm saying, Morris?

21:13.794 --> 21:16.231
[GRUNTING][MOANING]

21:16.275 --> 21:18.059
That's right.Oh, ow!

21:18.102 --> 21:19.539
My fucking shoulder.

21:19.582 --> 21:21.149
Stop complaining.
What would Jimmy Gold
do, huh?

21:21.192 --> 21:22.716
What would Jimmy do?
Give me some.

21:22.759 --> 21:24.413
Come on, that's my boy.
That's my boy. That's my boy.

21:24.457 --> 21:25.501
My rib!
My rib!

21:29.592 --> 21:31.768
Hey, they found the boat,
so we got a bonus.

21:31.812 --> 21:32.726
Great.

21:33.901 --> 21:34.945
Good job.

21:41.169 --> 21:45.521
Anything and everything
you guys can dig up
on Judge Bernard Raines.

21:47.523 --> 21:50.004
Lou's life might rest
in his hands.

21:50.047 --> 21:51.222
I need a background check.

21:52.441 --> 21:54.356
I want you to find out
everything you can,

21:54.400 --> 21:56.053
his likes, his dislikes,
his hobbies...

21:56.097 --> 21:57.664
Anything and everything
to get an inside track.

21:58.839 --> 22:00.797
Okay.Fucking guy scares me.

22:09.806 --> 22:11.547
You really think
he was just pretty good?

22:15.029 --> 22:18.249
I liked the book,
okay?

22:18.293 --> 22:19.468
I liked Jimmy Gold.

22:21.165 --> 22:22.166
But?

22:25.169 --> 22:26.562
But...

22:29.435 --> 22:30.349
There's too much anger.

22:33.003 --> 22:34.744
Look, I read up
on Rothstein,

22:34.788 --> 22:36.746
and the guy was angry,

22:36.790 --> 22:38.400
and it just oozes out
in that book.

22:40.750 --> 22:41.577
I also read that

22:43.449 --> 22:45.364
reading his books can

22:45.407 --> 22:48.410
breed melancholy
into teenage boys.

22:48.454 --> 22:51.021
It's like, uh,
swallowing a bad drug.

22:54.242 --> 22:55.461
So after I read The Runner,

22:55.504 --> 22:56.375
I couldn't help but think
of you...

22:59.029 --> 23:00.291
Your anger.

23:03.860 --> 23:06.297
I couldn't help but think

23:06.341 --> 23:08.299
maybe this book
cultivated some of it...

23:10.214 --> 23:12.391
Your perpetual discontent.

23:21.487 --> 23:22.836
I did read up
on the judge some.

23:25.447 --> 23:26.535
Okay.

23:26.883 --> 23:27.623
Well,

23:29.059 --> 23:31.453
I know where he drinks.

23:31.497 --> 23:33.455
It's a bar called, um,
Burtons.

23:34.630 --> 23:35.675
Okay.

23:37.111 --> 23:39.635
You might could
happen in for a pint

23:39.679 --> 23:42.029
and then get a good sense
of which way he's leaning.

23:42.072 --> 23:44.074
Then after the pint,
maybe you could, uh,

23:44.118 --> 23:45.206
influence him.

23:47.251 --> 23:49.079
[PHONE RINGS]

23:49.123 --> 23:51.081
HOLLY: Finders Keepers.

23:51.125 --> 23:53.040
Burtons, you said?Mm-hmm, on Willoughby.

23:53.083 --> 23:55.869
One second.
Bill, it's Montez.

23:55.912 --> 23:57.479
He says it's important.

23:57.523 --> 23:59.525
TONY: Got the location
from an anonymous tip.

24:01.396 --> 24:02.441
You think
this is our third man?

24:03.137 --> 24:04.660
Seems like it.

24:05.356 --> 24:07.358
The tire treads match.

24:07.402 --> 24:09.273
That information
is just for you,
by the way.

24:10.318 --> 24:11.450
What about the stolen goods?

24:12.407 --> 24:13.495
Nothing.

24:13.539 --> 24:14.888
No money.
Books?

24:15.671 --> 24:16.672
Nothing.

24:18.108 --> 24:18.892
[INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

24:18.935 --> 24:20.371
Got an ID?

24:20.415 --> 24:22.591
TONY: Not yet.

24:22.635 --> 24:24.463
There's not much left
of a face to look at.

24:24.506 --> 24:27.291
My guess is, he was ugly.

24:29.250 --> 24:30.860
How do you figure?

24:30.904 --> 24:32.253
I got a sense
for these things.

24:32.296 --> 24:33.341
He was ugly.

24:35.212 --> 24:36.910
[INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

24:39.782 --> 24:42.176
Was there a fourth man,
do you think?

24:42.219 --> 24:43.220
No evidence of it.

24:44.874 --> 24:47.137
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

24:47.181 --> 24:49.662
So if no fourth man,

24:49.705 --> 24:52.578
no money
or manuscripts here...

24:52.621 --> 24:54.188
Then somebody else
came along and
helped themselves.

24:56.582 --> 24:58.888
[BUZZER BLARES]

24:58.932 --> 25:02.109
Well, maybe
we could change venue

25:02.152 --> 25:03.153
if he's that nuts.

25:05.112 --> 25:06.113
He's not gonna kick it, Lou.

25:07.984 --> 25:09.943
There's too much
political pressure
to try it here.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.209
If I could get it down
to seven years...

25:20.997 --> 25:22.433
You said you
could win this.

25:23.260 --> 25:25.132
And that is still possible,

25:25.175 --> 25:26.307
but the risk is...

25:26.350 --> 25:27.656
I saved people.

25:27.700 --> 25:30.180
Even so,
Sarah Pace is excellent.

25:31.965 --> 25:34.576
If she appeals to the jury
to follow the law

25:34.620 --> 25:36.665
or uphold their oath...

25:36.709 --> 25:39.102
[SCOFFS SOFTLY]

25:39.146 --> 25:41.452
Vigilantism fares better
in the movies
than in real life.

25:44.847 --> 25:48.459
You said
we could win this.

25:48.503 --> 25:51.550
We can, and I will try,
but I...

25:51.593 --> 25:52.986
I'm not doing
seven years.

25:53.029 --> 25:54.117
I'm not.

25:54.161 --> 25:55.379
No to seven years.

25:59.383 --> 26:01.821
[FAINT ICE CREAM TRUCK MUSIC]

26:01.864 --> 26:03.736
♪

26:07.261 --> 26:08.523
You gotta get me
out of here.

26:09.350 --> 26:11.221
♪

26:13.267 --> 26:14.485
He...

26:15.835 --> 26:17.619
♪

26:19.229 --> 26:20.666
He finds me in here.

26:21.841 --> 26:23.886
♪

26:27.237 --> 26:28.238
Who finds you?

26:29.849 --> 26:31.590
♪

26:32.634 --> 26:33.592
Brady.

26:35.028 --> 26:37.073
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

26:37.117 --> 26:38.248
Brady?

26:39.554 --> 26:41.425
Brady Hartsfield?

26:41.469 --> 26:43.819
[WHISPERING]
He finds me in here.

26:43.863 --> 26:45.516
♪

26:48.824 --> 26:49.782
What do you mean?

26:50.870 --> 26:53.263
♪

26:55.004 --> 26:56.658
He finds me in here...
[SNIFFLES]

26:59.530 --> 27:00.706
And he talks to me.

27:03.056 --> 27:04.057
And I...

27:12.282 --> 27:15.024
All I'm saying is that
of all the people,

27:15.068 --> 27:18.462
John Rothstein was one
of the only things

27:18.506 --> 27:19.942
that Bridgton could
actually take pride in.

27:21.727 --> 27:23.903
He... Okay, but he never
took pride in us.

27:25.339 --> 27:27.689
I mean, he never...
He never gave anything.

27:27.733 --> 27:29.648
He never donated
to the town.

27:31.084 --> 27:32.346
You know,
and all that hoarding
he did

27:32.389 --> 27:33.869
was pretty damn stupid,
if you ask me.

27:35.001 --> 27:36.698
I say he invited
what happened to him.

27:36.742 --> 27:40.833
Even so, first the...
Other thing

27:40.876 --> 27:42.095
and then this.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.359
Another reason
to ban guns, I suppose.

27:45.402 --> 27:46.882
We'll never ban guns.

27:49.580 --> 27:51.408
I mean, the more people
feel oppressed,

27:51.452 --> 27:53.019
especially by government,

27:53.062 --> 27:54.585
the more they cling
to their right to bear arms.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.241
Government's the enemy.

27:58.285 --> 27:59.721
Once we hit
the tipping point...

27:59.765 --> 28:00.679
Where are you getting
all this?

28:01.157 --> 28:02.811
History books.

28:02.855 --> 28:04.770
It's how this
country started:

28:04.813 --> 28:06.772
citizens arming themselves
against government oppression.

28:07.816 --> 28:09.296
Uh-huh.
So the, uh...

28:09.339 --> 28:10.776
The people are
gonna overthrow
the government.

28:10.819 --> 28:11.907
Is that it?

28:11.951 --> 28:13.822
All it takes
is one bad king, right?

28:13.866 --> 28:15.215
Well, we don't have
a king, Peter.

28:15.258 --> 28:16.695
We have a democracy.

28:16.738 --> 28:18.131
What did
Winston Churchill say?

28:18.174 --> 28:20.133
"The best case
against democracy

28:20.176 --> 28:22.135
"is a five-minute conversation
with the average voter."

28:22.178 --> 28:24.877
Okay, can we just
eat dinner tonight

28:24.920 --> 28:27.749
without debating
what's wrong
with democracy

28:27.793 --> 28:28.924
or the world?

28:29.925 --> 28:30.883
Okay.

28:32.275 --> 28:33.537
Can we?

28:36.366 --> 28:37.672
Thank you.

28:37.716 --> 28:39.152
Spaghetti, please.Mm-hmm.

28:45.767 --> 28:48.335
"There was only one..."
No, wait.

28:48.378 --> 28:51.904
"I only committed
one crime in my life,

28:51.947 --> 28:54.210
"but it was
the worst sin of all."

28:55.908 --> 28:57.126
"Being born human."

28:57.823 --> 28:59.476
Second novel,

28:59.520 --> 29:00.826
when Jimmy's talking
to the priest.

29:01.565 --> 29:03.742
Very good.Yeah.

29:04.394 --> 29:05.961
Name of Jimmy's car.

29:07.354 --> 29:09.791
Oh, "Shadow Fear,"
same as Sitting Bull's
horse.

29:12.054 --> 29:14.230
Yeah, he always favored
the Indians.

29:14.274 --> 29:15.971
I thought we were asking
hard questions here.

29:17.451 --> 29:18.626
Jimmy's first love.

29:19.148 --> 29:19.888
Susan.

29:21.542 --> 29:22.499
Wrong.

29:24.023 --> 29:25.415
She was his first lay,
but he never loved her.

29:26.852 --> 29:28.244
Okay, well,
I know this, then.

29:28.288 --> 29:29.202
Um...

29:30.420 --> 29:32.205
The schoolteacher,

29:32.248 --> 29:34.598
the blonde that he went
skating with that time.

29:35.556 --> 29:38.080
Anne!
Anne with an E.

29:38.124 --> 29:39.081
There we go.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.782
Though didn't he end up
with Susan in the last book?

29:45.435 --> 29:47.437
He never loved her.[LAUGHS]

29:52.007 --> 29:56.359
What are the three things
a man must never do?

29:59.275 --> 30:00.711
Never apologize,

30:01.930 --> 30:02.975
never explain,

30:04.454 --> 30:05.804
never ask a woman

30:06.717 --> 30:08.067
if she came.

30:08.110 --> 30:09.329
[LAUGHS]

30:09.372 --> 30:10.809
Rothstein never did.

30:11.810 --> 30:13.376
[LAUGHS]

30:13.420 --> 30:14.508
Okay, bonus question.

30:16.902 --> 30:18.729
The only character to appear
in all three books,

30:20.035 --> 30:22.690
uh, other than Jimmy
or his car.

30:23.343 --> 30:24.170
All three?

30:24.213 --> 30:25.301
Yeah.

30:25.693 --> 30:26.912
Um...

30:31.742 --> 30:32.874
I don't know any.

30:33.657 --> 30:34.702
His mother.

30:35.659 --> 30:36.965
Bit of a trick question.

30:37.009 --> 30:38.706
She's a ghost
in the last two,
but still.

30:39.620 --> 30:40.882
You lose.
Take your top off.

30:40.926 --> 30:42.492
[LAUGHS]

30:44.364 --> 30:46.322
Mm.

30:46.366 --> 30:47.541
Oh, God.

30:57.464 --> 30:58.813
Hard to believe.

31:03.513 --> 31:04.950
You know,
he isn't really gone.

31:07.474 --> 31:08.910
Rothstein is,

31:10.738 --> 31:14.089
but Jimmy is forever.

31:17.136 --> 31:18.528
He lives in these books...

31:23.707 --> 31:25.361
And he lives a little
in you.

31:34.327 --> 31:35.632
[GLASSES CLINK]

31:36.503 --> 31:38.374
[PRINTER WHIRRING]

31:40.855 --> 31:42.335
[GROANS]

31:50.386 --> 31:53.128
What are you doing?

31:53.172 --> 31:56.044
Oh, this whole area
is ripe for redevelopment.

31:56.436 --> 31:57.741
Eminent domain.

31:57.785 --> 31:59.352
Right now,
it's no-man's-ville.

31:59.395 --> 32:02.616
If it gets rezoned
for business or commercial,

32:02.659 --> 32:04.835
a little
suburban redevelopment,

32:04.879 --> 32:06.141
this could be
a gold mine.

32:06.185 --> 32:08.317
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

32:08.361 --> 32:10.058
Up off Route Six?

32:11.712 --> 32:13.105
What kind of business
would want to locate there?

32:15.194 --> 32:17.326
Tech. Big Data.

32:17.370 --> 32:18.501
Big Tech.

32:24.464 --> 32:25.682
What are you writing?

32:26.814 --> 32:27.554
People who live there.

32:29.599 --> 32:31.427
What scheme
are you hatching, Morrie?

32:32.994 --> 32:34.517
Gonna start, like,
a real estate fund now?

32:37.216 --> 32:39.566
No official statement
from the police,

32:39.609 --> 32:41.394
but sources say
that this crash

32:41.437 --> 32:43.178
may be related
to the Rothstein mur...

32:43.222 --> 32:44.963
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
I-I want to see this.

32:45.006 --> 32:47.226
The vehicle
had been reported stolen,

32:47.269 --> 32:48.792
and a box of latex gloves

32:48.836 --> 32:50.446
had been found inside.

32:50.490 --> 32:52.013
You'll recall
that latex gloves

32:52.057 --> 32:53.884
were discovered
on Carl Fenten,

32:53.928 --> 32:56.104
who was found dead
in the Rothstein house,

32:56.148 --> 32:59.325
the victim of a gunshot wound to the neck.

32:59.368 --> 33:01.457
What are you doing?
I said I wanted
to watch that.

33:01.501 --> 33:02.719
Turn that on!

33:02.763 --> 33:04.243
We need to have
a conversation.About what?

33:04.286 --> 33:05.200
You need to sit down.

33:07.202 --> 33:08.160
Sit down.

33:13.513 --> 33:15.210
We need to talk
about John Rothstein.

33:16.733 --> 33:18.039
What do you mean?

33:18.083 --> 33:20.346
What do I mean?
I mean, seriously?

33:23.218 --> 33:24.698
What are you
talking about,
Danielle?

33:27.222 --> 33:28.180
What are you
talking about?

33:31.096 --> 33:36.101
You know how you said
that you escaped into books
when you were a kid?

33:37.450 --> 33:40.801
I mean, it was the dead guy
on TV, wasn't it?

33:40.844 --> 33:42.107
His books?

33:43.108 --> 33:45.066
And suddenly he's killed,

33:47.112 --> 33:49.592
and you don't want to leave
the apartment anymore.

33:51.899 --> 33:53.857
You don't think that I see
the connection there?

33:59.646 --> 34:00.690
You're grieving, Morrie.

34:02.779 --> 34:05.043
You're mourning
your big hero,

34:05.086 --> 34:08.263
like he's...
Bobby Orr or something.

34:17.142 --> 34:18.317
Maybe.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.147
Maybe.

34:28.414 --> 34:29.197
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

34:31.895 --> 34:32.940
Hey, bud.

34:39.164 --> 34:40.121
I, uh...

34:45.605 --> 34:48.129
[SIGHS] I wanted
to apologize to you

34:50.436 --> 34:52.133
for accusing you
of selling drugs.

34:52.177 --> 34:54.092
I just, uh...It's okay.

34:58.444 --> 35:01.403
You know,
I was sitting there
at dinner tonight

35:01.447 --> 35:03.318
listening to you talk,
and I just thought...

35:06.234 --> 35:08.280
"Who is this smart kid
sitting at my table?"

35:13.154 --> 35:14.764
When that car
ran me down, Pete,

35:16.897 --> 35:18.594
when that monster
ran me down,

35:21.597 --> 35:22.816
man, I just stopped.

35:25.688 --> 35:28.996
I threw up
all these walls
around me

35:29.039 --> 35:30.563
and I walled
everything out:

35:30.606 --> 35:32.739
you, your mom,
everybody, everything.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.265
I had this beautiful
12-year-old boy

35:38.658 --> 35:40.399
that I stopped being
a decent dad to.

35:43.619 --> 35:46.361
I stopped being there
for you and your mom.

35:48.407 --> 35:50.017
But I'm coming back, Pete.

35:53.629 --> 35:57.372
And I'm not even halfway
to halfway there yet,

35:58.634 --> 35:59.853
but I'm coming back.

36:05.902 --> 36:06.642
What you reading?

36:08.862 --> 36:10.168
Oh, school stuff.

36:11.256 --> 36:12.170
Mm.

36:15.390 --> 36:16.565
Looks old.

36:18.306 --> 36:19.351
Just primary source
from the library.

36:21.657 --> 36:23.398
Oh.

36:23.442 --> 36:24.312
I'll leave you to it.

36:32.668 --> 36:34.888
[SLOW ROCK MUSIC]

36:36.281 --> 36:37.412
[SIGHS]

36:39.284 --> 36:41.111
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

36:42.765 --> 36:44.593
♪

36:46.291 --> 36:47.640
Oh, but Ali...

36:47.683 --> 36:50.077
Ali was the best
at it of all of...

36:52.297 --> 36:54.037
Evening, Your Honor.

36:54.081 --> 36:57.258
You're here ex parte.
You know that, right?

36:57.302 --> 36:58.216
What?

36:59.869 --> 37:02.263
That's Latin
for "beat it."

37:02.307 --> 37:03.308
Hmm?

37:05.484 --> 37:06.963
Hey, Derek.

37:07.007 --> 37:08.226
You got it, Judge.Yeah.

37:10.140 --> 37:12.273
♪

37:16.321 --> 37:17.452
And you, sir?

37:19.933 --> 37:21.326
Exactly how nuts
are you?

37:25.155 --> 37:28.594
Just the right amount,
hmm?

37:28.637 --> 37:31.466
Enough for you to tell
your pal Finkelfuck

37:32.206 --> 37:33.686
he better plead
this thing out.

37:35.862 --> 37:38.734
Listen, I'm not one
for telling judges
how to judge...

37:38.778 --> 37:40.258
Well, that's smart.

37:40.301 --> 37:41.911
But you seem
a bit off the fairway

37:41.955 --> 37:44.262
to be playing Solomon
with your own dick,

37:44.305 --> 37:45.437
much less
other people's lives.

37:46.089 --> 37:49.658
[LAUGHS]
I like that.

37:49.702 --> 37:51.486
Are you a fan
of the law
or not?

37:54.489 --> 37:56.448
The law doesn't
always work,
Mr. Hodges.

37:56.491 --> 37:58.711
Depends on who's doing
the administrating.

37:58.754 --> 38:00.278
And in my courtroom,
that'd be me.

38:02.497 --> 38:04.499
As long as I can keep
my seat, that is.

38:05.718 --> 38:07.459
For me to be in business,
I got to stay in business,

38:08.590 --> 38:11.158
which means I got
to play the populist

38:11.201 --> 38:13.116
every now and again
in order to get reelected,

38:14.379 --> 38:18.252
which means
those traditional
judicial boundaries

38:18.296 --> 38:20.167
you see
in your rearview mirror,

38:22.212 --> 38:23.692
way tinier than
they appear,

38:25.215 --> 38:27.392
which means
at the end of the day,

38:27.435 --> 38:29.132
I let my conscience
be my guide,

38:30.830 --> 38:33.311
which will not bode well
for Lou Linklatter.

38:35.225 --> 38:36.879
"Later."

38:36.923 --> 38:38.490
It's Lou "Link-later."

38:39.752 --> 38:41.928
"Latter," "Later."

38:41.971 --> 38:43.930
You tell Finkelfuck

38:43.973 --> 38:45.453
to plead this thing out.

38:46.672 --> 38:48.717
♪

38:52.591 --> 38:53.983
That's what I keep
telling you.

38:54.027 --> 38:55.985
She won't plea.
That's the thing.

38:56.029 --> 38:57.813
Not even
to any time?

38:57.857 --> 39:00.338
She'd rather roll the dice
with the trial.
She just wants out.

39:00.381 --> 39:01.426
Well, is that
at all possible?

39:01.469 --> 39:02.601
I mean, could she get out?

39:02.644 --> 39:04.342
It is, but only
if we go quickly.

39:04.385 --> 39:05.604
Because?

39:05.647 --> 39:08.389
She's regressing
mentally.

39:08.433 --> 39:11.914
For Lou to win,
she would need
to testify.

39:11.958 --> 39:14.177
She would need
to be credible,
relatable.

39:14.221 --> 39:16.266
She is losing
her relatable fastball.

39:18.051 --> 39:20.619
She says
Brady Hartsfield
is visiting her.

39:22.838 --> 39:23.578
I beg your pardon?

39:25.014 --> 39:25.928
That's what she says.

39:27.408 --> 39:28.844
She hears him.

39:28.888 --> 39:30.716
She hears his voice.

39:31.891 --> 39:33.283
[SCOFFS]

39:33.327 --> 39:35.198
Incarceration
is not working for her,

39:35.242 --> 39:36.548
which is why we need
to go fast.

39:40.813 --> 39:42.554
There's only six families
that live

39:42.597 --> 39:43.990
in the immediate area
of the crash site.

39:44.033 --> 39:46.645
I know the ones
who live there,
the Krantzes.

39:46.688 --> 39:48.473
90s.
No way they're
taking walks.

39:49.474 --> 39:51.127
Younger family
lives here.

39:51.171 --> 39:53.086
Saw a teenage kid.
They have a dog too.

39:53.129 --> 39:54.043
Dogs need exercise.

39:55.828 --> 39:58.961
Maybe I should knock
on some doors
selling my honey,

39:59.005 --> 40:01.094
get a bit of a look-see
as to who's who.

40:01.137 --> 40:03.139
I got a nose for thieves,
you know,

40:03.183 --> 40:05.098
and a hankering.

40:05.141 --> 40:06.839
I'm not a thief.You're not a thief?

40:06.882 --> 40:08.971
I'm just trying to turn
a fucking corner, okay?

40:09.015 --> 40:10.408
That's all.

40:10.451 --> 40:11.670
A little touchy,
Morris.

40:11.713 --> 40:12.975
[SIGHS][MARKER CLATTERS]

40:13.019 --> 40:14.063
You okay?

40:15.108 --> 40:17.066
You're blinking
your eyes a lot.

40:17.110 --> 40:18.416
When you blink
your eyes a lot,
it's...

40:23.029 --> 40:24.378
Tell me.

40:26.641 --> 40:27.468
I just...

40:29.644 --> 40:31.211
Can't shake what I did,
who I did it to.

40:33.256 --> 40:34.475
Ah.

40:36.172 --> 40:37.783
They're saying
on the news that...

40:39.088 --> 40:40.438
I murdered culture,

40:42.788 --> 40:45.268
that what I did was worse
than the Mr. Mercedes guy,

40:46.661 --> 40:48.707
'cause he just
killed losers,

40:48.750 --> 40:50.360
while whoever killed
John Rothstein murdered...

40:53.102 --> 40:54.103
Greatness,

40:55.453 --> 40:56.715
which is exactly
what I did.

40:58.717 --> 40:59.979
[SIGHS]

41:02.982 --> 41:05.680
When I got my diabetes,
I was in dire straits.

41:05.724 --> 41:06.638
No insurance.

41:07.813 --> 41:09.510
I went to John
to ask him for help.

41:10.816 --> 41:11.686
We'd been lovers,

41:12.470 --> 41:14.123
friends, so I thought.

41:14.167 --> 41:15.516
You know what he told me?

41:17.387 --> 41:19.433
He said I should
go to India,

41:19.477 --> 41:21.261
first because
the medical care

41:21.304 --> 41:23.045
was cheaper and better
over there,

41:23.089 --> 41:24.525
and second,

41:24.569 --> 41:26.701
since I had come
to resemble a cow,

41:28.094 --> 41:29.443
they would revere me,

41:29.487 --> 41:31.184
pursuant to their
Hindu beliefs.

41:32.577 --> 41:34.535
That's what
he said to me

41:34.579 --> 41:36.668
in my time of sickness
and need.

41:38.234 --> 41:40.628
"Go to India,
you fat cow."

41:42.151 --> 41:44.589
I had a great hatred
for John Rothstein
after that,

41:45.981 --> 41:48.157
but my animus softened
with the realization

41:48.201 --> 41:50.377
that he was simply
a product
of our society,

41:52.205 --> 41:55.034
where the wealthy
not only fail to help
the less fortunate

41:55.077 --> 41:57.732
but find ways
to condemn them.

41:57.776 --> 42:00.430
We live in the richest country
in the world, Morris,

42:00.474 --> 42:02.563
where we get to eat cake.

42:02.607 --> 42:05.044
We don't get educated.
We don't get health care.

42:05.087 --> 42:07.394
We don't get living wages.
We don't get shit.

42:09.527 --> 42:11.529
John Rothstein embodied
the privileged few.

42:12.747 --> 42:16.403
Rich, uncaring,
exalting his tax breaks

42:16.446 --> 42:18.536
over compassion
for human suffering.

42:19.928 --> 42:21.626
Well, guess what.

42:21.669 --> 42:22.888
Comes a time
of reckoning.

42:24.063 --> 42:25.543
Killing John Rothstein,

42:26.631 --> 42:28.415
that makes you a hero
in my book.

42:29.242 --> 42:30.460
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

42:30.504 --> 42:32.593
And you'd be a hero
in John's book as well.

42:33.333 --> 42:34.377
How do you figure?

42:34.421 --> 42:36.728
Well, who did
Jimmy Gold admire?

42:36.771 --> 42:40.645
Sam Adams, Daniel Shays,
the Molly Maguires.

42:40.688 --> 42:43.430
Where are those beacons today
to rise up against injustice?

42:45.606 --> 42:48.348
You're the new
Jimmy Gold,
Morris,

42:48.391 --> 42:49.697
the modern-day
Thomas Paine.

42:51.220 --> 42:52.352
[EERIE MUSIC]

42:52.395 --> 42:54.615
And like with
all revolutions,

42:54.659 --> 42:56.399
it requires
bloodshed.

42:58.010 --> 42:59.577
John Rothstein
was a good start.

43:01.404 --> 43:03.189
Whoever took the books,

43:03.232 --> 43:05.452
your books,

43:05.495 --> 43:06.627
your money...

43:07.976 --> 43:09.761
♪

43:09.804 --> 43:11.501
He's next.

43:11.545 --> 43:14.417
CROWD: [CHANTING]
Let Lou go! Let Lou go!

43:14.461 --> 43:17.769
Let Lou go!
Let Lou go!

43:17.812 --> 43:20.685
Let Lou go! Let Lou go!Back up for me, please.

43:20.728 --> 43:23.252
CROWD: [CHANTING]
Let Lou go! Let Lou go!

43:23.296 --> 43:25.254
Detective Hodges,

43:25.298 --> 43:26.473
could I get a comment,
any statement?

43:26.516 --> 43:27.648
Not today.

43:27.692 --> 43:29.302
Are you hopeful
for justice,

43:29.345 --> 43:31.478
and would your idea
of that be in this case?

43:31.521 --> 43:33.567
HODGES: My idea of justice
doesn't carry the day.

43:33.611 --> 43:35.090
Would that it did.

43:35.134 --> 43:37.440
CROWD: [CHANTING]
Let Lou go! Let Lou go!

43:37.484 --> 43:38.877
But I do say this:

43:41.706 --> 43:44.360
the people's will,
you know...
It matters.

43:44.404 --> 43:45.623
It matters in their hearts.

43:45.666 --> 43:47.755
It matters in the voting booth.

43:47.799 --> 43:52.238
I'm glad to see public assembly such as this here.

43:52.281 --> 43:54.849
Not too long ago, people were too terrified to gather in crowds

43:54.893 --> 43:57.765
for fear of the oncoming grille of a speeding car.

43:59.506 --> 44:00.986
That terror has been eradicated,

44:01.029 --> 44:03.423
extinguished by Lou Linklatter,

44:03.466 --> 44:05.338
so I'm heartened

44:05.381 --> 44:08.602
to see her heroism recognized today

44:08.646 --> 44:10.473
by the will
of the people.

44:10.517 --> 44:13.738
We can only hope
that legal justice

44:13.781 --> 44:15.653
rises up to the conscience of the common man.

44:16.871 --> 44:18.220
Pathetic.

44:18.264 --> 44:19.439
Thank you.

44:20.440 --> 44:22.355
That was impressive.

44:22.398 --> 44:24.139
What that was,
was a farce.

44:24.183 --> 44:27.055
It's the media tail waving
the justice dog by the balls.

44:27.099 --> 44:28.317
First those whores
in Washington,

44:28.361 --> 44:29.884
now the judges.

44:29.928 --> 44:32.495
Hear ye, hear ye.
Justice dog by the balls.

44:32.539 --> 44:34.149
[LAUGHS]

44:34.193 --> 44:35.281
All rise.

44:36.761 --> 44:38.110
This court is
now in session.

44:38.153 --> 44:40.590
The honorable Judge
Bernard Raines presiding.

44:42.636 --> 44:45.378
Hello, everybody.
[CHUCKLES]

44:45.421 --> 44:49.338
Nice to wake up
in the grand state of Ohio

44:49.382 --> 44:51.558
to this warm sunshine, huh,

44:51.601 --> 44:53.038
in the month of February?

44:53.081 --> 44:54.213
Huh? Sit.

44:58.391 --> 45:00.567
Madam Prosecutor,

45:00.610 --> 45:01.524
what have you got for me?

45:05.180 --> 45:08.183
The People of Ohio
stand ready for trial,
Your Honor.

45:09.402 --> 45:11.578
I beg your pardon?

45:11.621 --> 45:13.885
The People of Ohio
stand ready for trial.

45:15.016 --> 45:16.714
Mm-hmm.

45:20.152 --> 45:21.588
Mr. Finkelstein,

45:21.631 --> 45:23.111
something you want to say?

45:23.938 --> 45:24.722
Yes, Judge, I do.

45:27.333 --> 45:28.595
At this time,

45:28.638 --> 45:30.945
we would amend
our pleadings

45:30.989 --> 45:33.948
and affirmative defenses
to include necessity.

45:35.994 --> 45:37.778
Mm, okay.
Necessity.

45:39.737 --> 45:42.696
Well, I'm a big believer
in doing what's necessary.

45:42.740 --> 45:44.132
Will the defendant
please rise?

45:46.482 --> 45:48.963
[RAINES CLEARING THROAT]

45:49.007 --> 45:53.925
First, based on a lack
of sustainable evidence,

45:53.968 --> 45:57.755
I hereby am excluding
self-defense

45:57.798 --> 46:00.192
as your affirmative defense,
so that's... That's gone too.

46:00.235 --> 46:02.368
You can't do that!Your objection is noted,

46:02.411 --> 46:04.413
Counsel, and overruled,

46:04.457 --> 46:06.459
because I absolutely
can do that,

46:06.502 --> 46:08.809
and I hereby do so,
and furthermore,

46:08.853 --> 46:12.682
if you so much
as suggest

46:12.726 --> 46:15.860
that your client acted
in self-defense to a jury,

46:15.903 --> 46:18.471
I will hold you
in contempt,

46:18.514 --> 46:19.994
and by now,
you should be comfortable

46:20.038 --> 46:22.954
knowing that I mean
what I say.

46:22.997 --> 46:27.262
So that leaves you
with necessity.

46:27.306 --> 46:30.178
Are you sure
there's not some rethinking

46:30.222 --> 46:32.224
you might want to do
before we proceed?

46:34.487 --> 46:35.618
No, Your Honor.

46:37.403 --> 46:40.014
The defense remains ready
for trial.

46:40.058 --> 46:41.799
Is that right,
Miss Linklatter?

46:46.673 --> 46:51.504
You ready to, uh,
roll the dice
with necessity?

46:51.547 --> 46:53.288
Hello? Miss Linklatter,
I'm talking to you.

46:53.332 --> 46:54.289
Yes, Your Honor.

46:55.247 --> 46:57.510
Are you prepared
to roll the dice

46:57.553 --> 47:00.252
with, uh, necessity

47:00.295 --> 47:02.080
as your sole defense?

47:02.123 --> 47:03.733
Yes, sir... Your Honor.

47:08.347 --> 47:10.653
Are you all right,
Miss Linklatter?

47:13.047 --> 47:14.353
You look a little
traumatized.

47:14.396 --> 47:15.310
Are you okay?

47:17.008 --> 47:17.965
I've had...

47:21.926 --> 47:23.318
Better days.

47:23.362 --> 47:24.624
I bet you have.

47:29.542 --> 47:31.979
Before we proceed

47:32.023 --> 47:34.242
with our never-ending,

47:34.286 --> 47:37.289
unflinching quest
for justice...

47:40.466 --> 47:43.034
I feel duty-bound
to make sure

47:43.077 --> 47:46.080
that your head
is in proper
working order,

47:46.124 --> 47:48.866
so pursuant
to Provision 46B

47:48.909 --> 47:50.563
of the Ohio Criminal Code,

47:51.956 --> 47:54.872
I'm ordering that
the defendant be transferred

47:54.915 --> 47:56.699
to the mental
facility in...What?

47:56.743 --> 47:58.963
Columbus for a period
of not...

47:59.006 --> 48:01.226
Not less than four weeks,
not more than a year,

48:01.269 --> 48:03.184
in order that you
may be tested...Your Honor!

48:03.228 --> 48:07.754
In order to make sure
that you are mentally
competent to stand trial.

48:07.797 --> 48:09.887
Objection!
There is no evidence

48:09.930 --> 48:11.453
to support
a competency test!

48:11.497 --> 48:13.064
Nor am I asking for one,
Your Honor.

48:13.107 --> 48:14.674
JUDGE RAINES: I don't
need your permission!

48:14.717 --> 48:15.893
And what's your source?

48:18.156 --> 48:20.114
I'm looking at her,
and she don't look right,

48:20.158 --> 48:21.899
so I got to
make a call.

48:22.421 --> 48:24.510
Sua sponte.

48:24.553 --> 48:26.904
You know what sua sponte
means, Counsels?

48:26.947 --> 48:29.558
Huh?
It's Latin...

48:29.602 --> 48:33.562
For "I get to do
whatever I want
because I'm the judge."

48:33.606 --> 48:35.434
Take the defendant
back into custody.

48:35.477 --> 48:36.826
Finkelstein,
this is what you said...
You said this wouldn't happen.

48:36.870 --> 48:38.132
Your Honor,
you can't do this!

48:38.176 --> 48:39.742
[MOCKINGLY] "Your Honor,
you can't do this."

48:39.786 --> 48:41.135
They're not going to do it.
I'm gonna get
you out of there.

48:41.179 --> 48:42.963
JUDGE RAINES:
Why does nobody
listen to me?

48:43.007 --> 48:44.443
You fucking lied.I did not lie.

48:44.486 --> 48:46.140
I promise you.

48:46.184 --> 48:48.577
JUDGE RAINES:
Nobody listens to me.
I tried to tell you,

48:48.621 --> 48:52.407
but now you
got sua sponte,

48:52.451 --> 48:55.149
she gets her head examined,
and we are adjourned!

48:55.193 --> 48:56.629
Nobody ever listens.

48:56.672 --> 48:57.978
That's the damn trouble
with these people.

48:58.022 --> 48:59.937
[CROWD MURMURING]

49:03.984 --> 49:06.117
Hey.
How was your day?Fine.

49:07.379 --> 49:08.380
Got a lot of homework.

49:09.859 --> 49:12.297
Wait, aren't you gonna
have dinner first?

49:12.340 --> 49:13.124
Pete!

49:25.527 --> 49:28.574
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

49:28.617 --> 49:31.359
♪

49:58.082 --> 50:00.475
MARJORIE:
Peter, honey!
Dinnertime!

50:00.519 --> 50:01.694
Be right there!

50:01.737 --> 50:04.131
♪

50:07.221 --> 50:08.788
TOM: Peter,
your mother called!

50:08.831 --> 50:10.442
Didn't you hear?Coming!

50:10.485 --> 50:13.227
♪

50:18.667 --> 50:19.668
JEROME: Good boy.

50:21.409 --> 50:23.194
I mean, is it
the worst thing?

50:23.237 --> 50:25.065
They deem her incompetent,
she won't be convicted.

50:25.892 --> 50:27.894
That's the way
I was thinking.

50:27.937 --> 50:29.852
Problem is,

50:29.896 --> 50:33.073
she can be kept
in the loony bin
in perpetuity,

50:33.117 --> 50:34.161
never even get to trial.

50:35.510 --> 50:36.511
Fuck.

50:39.514 --> 50:41.168
This is worse
than prison.

50:43.431 --> 50:46.521
I mean, these places
are not about healing you.

50:46.565 --> 50:49.307
They're not about helping
people get better.

50:49.350 --> 50:52.223
They're about sectioning off
the undesirables from society,

50:52.266 --> 50:54.051
you know, the people
that they deem icky,

50:54.094 --> 50:55.530
the people
that they deem sick.

50:55.574 --> 50:57.097
We are not sick.

51:00.100 --> 51:01.710
Sorry. I apologize.
That was...

51:02.450 --> 51:03.886
There's no need.

51:03.930 --> 51:05.714
You know, I just...
I used to be
in such a place,

51:05.758 --> 51:07.107
which I know
that you know,

51:07.151 --> 51:09.544
but it bears repeating,
'cause that's what I do.

51:09.588 --> 51:12.504
[CHUCKLES] I repeat myself
when I'm anxious and...

51:12.547 --> 51:16.377
Repeat and repeat
and repeat...
I'm sorry.

51:16.421 --> 51:19.467
It's unprofessional.
You know,
I'm meant to be...

51:19.511 --> 51:22.122
Sane during
business hours.

51:22.166 --> 51:24.124
I apologize.

51:24.168 --> 51:26.866
It's after business hours,
so it's okay.

51:26.909 --> 51:29.390
Holly,
we're all a bit mad.

51:29.434 --> 51:30.696
It's what makes us human.

51:31.697 --> 51:32.959
That and literature.

51:33.786 --> 51:35.440
[SCOFFS]
Right.

51:42.795 --> 51:45.319
You're the most human
of us all here.

51:45.363 --> 51:46.799
Well, most of the time.

51:49.628 --> 51:52.152
We look to that
humanity, you know?

51:52.196 --> 51:53.240
We even feed off it.

51:56.200 --> 51:57.157
Thank you.

52:00.160 --> 52:01.335
We're gonna be there for Lou.

52:03.642 --> 52:04.730
We just have
to get her out...

52:08.473 --> 52:10.997
You know, or she'll become
what they say she is.

52:13.869 --> 52:15.262
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

52:16.655 --> 52:19.353
[CELL PHONE CLICKS][SIGHS] Hodges.

52:19.397 --> 52:21.964
You want in the loop?
I give you "in the loop."

52:22.008 --> 52:24.228
You're gonna like this.

52:24.271 --> 52:26.360
This about shaking hands
with a corpse again?

52:26.404 --> 52:29.276
It's not about that,
and he happens
to be in there,

52:29.320 --> 52:30.756
should you care.

52:30.799 --> 52:32.236
I don't.

52:33.672 --> 52:35.195
Okay. Go ahead.

52:41.984 --> 52:43.377
And could you
lift his head?Mm-hmm.

52:45.597 --> 52:47.251
Okay, you see that,

52:47.294 --> 52:50.471
those two crater-sized holes
in the back of his head?

52:50.515 --> 52:52.865
Holes like that are not
created from a car crash.

52:52.908 --> 52:55.389
You can put his head down.

52:55.433 --> 52:57.217
And it's a little hard
to see what the fuck
is going on up front,

52:57.261 --> 52:59.828
but that there
looks like a bullet hole,

52:59.872 --> 53:02.440
and the autopsy showed
a projectile
going into his brain.

53:02.483 --> 53:03.571
Yeah, he was shot.

53:03.615 --> 53:05.225
And the holes
in the back

53:05.269 --> 53:06.661
had the threads
of a drill bit.

53:06.705 --> 53:08.228
But don't let me
steal your thunder,
tell him.

53:08.272 --> 53:10.230
We believe
he was fatally shot

53:10.274 --> 53:12.493
and that somebody used
a power drill

53:12.537 --> 53:13.799
to excavate the bullet.

53:13.842 --> 53:15.192
But there are no bone bits
or blood in his truck.

53:16.497 --> 53:18.195
He was killed
and then planted
in the truck.

53:18.238 --> 53:20.240
That's my thinking.

53:20.284 --> 53:21.589
This here is what we call
a dead herring.

53:22.851 --> 53:23.852
No?

53:26.377 --> 53:30.207
Hey, well, since we're here,
do you want to, uh, see him?

53:30.250 --> 53:31.599
Rothstein.
He's in there.

53:33.297 --> 53:34.689
Don't be
fucking morbid.

53:34.733 --> 53:36.256
I'm not being morbid,

53:36.300 --> 53:38.389
but I'm just saying,
you're in the same room
as him, Bill.

53:40.217 --> 53:42.262
I met the guy
when he was alive, okay?

53:42.306 --> 53:44.873
I don't need to see him dead
to check off my bucket list.

53:44.917 --> 53:47.267
This is your last chance.

53:50.705 --> 53:51.663
Oh, fine.

53:51.706 --> 53:52.707
Okay.

54:17.993 --> 54:20.518
Even in repose,
it's like

54:20.561 --> 54:21.736
looking at a Rockwell.

54:23.172 --> 54:24.261
This is a calling
for us, Bill.

54:26.915 --> 54:28.482
Catch the guy who killed him.

54:28.526 --> 54:29.962
It's a calling.

54:32.704 --> 54:33.705
Touch him.

54:35.359 --> 54:36.490
I'm not gonna touch him.

54:38.971 --> 54:40.102
Touch him.

54:40.929 --> 54:42.104
Don't be daft.

54:43.192 --> 54:44.716
It inspired me,
I'm telling you.

54:46.021 --> 54:47.936
There's something there,

54:47.980 --> 54:49.286
even dead,

54:51.288 --> 54:53.246
like... Magic.

54:55.814 --> 54:56.989
Touch him.

55:39.379 --> 55:41.381
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

55:46.255 --> 55:47.474
Hey.

55:48.606 --> 55:50.695
I just walked in.

55:50.738 --> 55:51.870
Bit of a long day.

55:51.913 --> 55:53.045
How's Seattle?

55:54.438 --> 55:55.352
Catch any salmon?

55:59.443 --> 56:01.575
Ah, no, just stuff at work,
you know.

56:01.619 --> 56:02.489
How's Allie?

56:05.666 --> 56:07.189
Nah.

56:07.233 --> 56:08.495
No, nobody's dead.

56:12.412 --> 56:13.587
Just tired.
That's all.

56:16.938 --> 56:18.287
Well...

56:21.421 --> 56:23.075
Actually...

56:25.294 --> 56:26.992
Someone is dead.

56:29.473 --> 56:32.432
Someone in particular,
which I suspect you know

56:32.476 --> 56:33.651
and is the reason
you're calling.

56:33.694 --> 56:34.652
Thank you.

56:36.915 --> 56:39.221
Ah, no, no.

56:39.265 --> 56:41.659
I'm good, other than that.

56:41.702 --> 56:44.401
Missing you, missing Allie,
but otherwise...

56:48.796 --> 56:50.711
[GROANS]

56:50.755 --> 56:52.017
Actually...

56:54.802 --> 56:57.022
Never mind.

56:57.065 --> 57:00.242
No, no, never mind.
Never mind.
Look, I'll just say it.

57:00.286 --> 57:02.462
You remember I said
that after Brady Hartsfield

57:02.506 --> 57:04.421
that my song was sung,

57:05.900 --> 57:07.946
that there'd never be
anybody else,

57:07.989 --> 57:09.904
I could go back to my paints,
there'd never be another?

57:13.125 --> 57:14.039
There's another.

